  "multipart_required": true,
  "full_prompt": "Design the primary pressure hull of an autonomous underwater vehicle benchmark as a multi-part sealed assembly consisting of the cylindrical aluminum barrel, a removable forward hemispherical endcap with O-ring flange, an integrated aft hemispherical endcap, the O-ring flange bolt set, and eight wet-mate penetrator bosses (4 M16 connectors + 2 thruster shafts + 1 acoustic transducer + 1 pressure port), operating in a test pool (38 ft / 11.6 m maximum depth). Vehicle displacement ~45 kg, hull diameter 200 mm OD, cylindrical length 500 mm with two hemispherical endcaps (one O-ring flange access, one integrated). Material: 6061-T6 aluminum (Young's modulus 68.9 GPa, Poisson 0.33, yield 276 MPa, ultimate 310 MPa, density 2700 kg/m^3), wall thickness nominal 6 mm cylinder + 5 mm endcaps, with anti-corrosion hard-anodized coating. Hull hosts 8 penetrators (4 M16 wet-mate connectors + 2 thruster shafts + 1 acoustic transducer + 1 pressure port). Design depth: 11.6 m freshwater + 2x safety factor = 23.2 m equivalent, giving MEOP 228 kPa external gauge. Load cases: (LC1) MEOP 228 kPa external (-0.228 MPa gauge inside cavity); (LC2) proof pressure 1.5 x MEOP = 342 kPa; (LC3) burst 2.5 x MEOP = 570 kPa must not ultimate-fail; (LC4) thruster reaction: 50 N thrust per thruster at two opposing penetrators produces +/- 100 N couple on hull endcaps; (LC5) handling drop: 1 m drop onto hard surface (10 g impulse); (LC6) O-ring flange preload: 8 x M6 bolts at 10 N-m torque = 18 kN total axial clamp on the flange; (LC7) thermal: fresh-water 15 C to tropical pool 30 C swing. Pass/fail per ANSI/AIAA S-080A + ASME BPVC VIII analog: (R1) max von Mises under LC1-LC2 <= 184 MPa (yield 276 / 1.5); (R2) burst LC3 no ultimate failure (stress <= 310 MPa); (R3) linear-buckling eigenvalue of external-pressure-loaded cylinder under LC1 >= 3.0; (R4) hull + endcap dry mass <= 8 kg; (R5) penetrator boss local stress under LC6 <= 184 MPa; (R6) hull first longitudinal mode above 150 Hz. Verification is performed on the assembled barrel + endcaps + flange bolts + penetrator bosses multi-body model with representative bolted + O-ring interface stiffness; per-part stress is reported but does not gate pass/fail. Deliverables: STEP AP242, pressure FEA per case, buckling eigenvalue, thermal FEA, modal, and mass report.",
  "short_prompt": "Design the primary pressure hull of an autonomous underwater vehicle benchmark operating in a test pool (38 ft / 11.6 m maximum depth).\n\nVehicle displacement ~45 kg, hull diameter 200 mm OD, cylindrical length 500 mm with two hemispherical endcaps. Material 6061-T6 aluminum (Young's modulus 68.9 GPa, Poisson 0.33, yield 276 MPa, ultimate 310 MPa, density 2700 kg/m^3), wall thickness nominal 6 mm cylinder + 5 mm endcaps, with anti-corrosion hard-anodized coating. Hull hosts 8 penetrators (4 M16 wet-mate connectors + 2 thruster shafts + 1 acoustic transducer + 1 pressure port). Design depth: 11.6 m freshwater + 2x safety factor = 23.2 m equivalent, giving MEOP 228 kPa external gauge.\n\nLoad cases: LC1 MEOP 228 kPa external; LC2 proof pressure 1.5 x MEOP = 342 kPa; LC3 burst 2.5 x MEOP = 570 kPa must not ultimate-fail; LC4 thruster reaction 50 N thrust per thruster producing +/- 100 N couple; LC5 handling drop 1 m onto hard surface (10 g impulse); LC6 O-ring flange preload 8 x M6 bolts at 10 N-m torque = 18 kN total axial clamp; LC7 thermal fresh-water 15 C to tropical pool 30 C swing.",
